    {
      "actionDate": "2025-02-26",
      "actionDesc": "Introduced in House",
      "text": "<p><strong>ThinkDIFFERENTLY About Disability Employment Act</strong></p><p>This bill requires the Small Business Administration (SBA) to (1) provide assistance to individuals with disabilities who desire to become entrepreneurs or to be self-employed, (2) help individuals with disabilities find employment at small businesses; and (3) assist small businesses with hiring such individuals and with accessibility issues applicable to such individuals.</p><p>The SBA must conduct outreach and education about such activities.</p><p>The bill establishes reporting requirements with respect to these activities.</p>",
      "updateDate": "2025-05-30T21:12:32Z",
      "versionCode": "00"
    }
  ]
